result.execSummary:
The defendant Tiffany Lynn Jelinski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Penalty-Theft if Value <=$2500], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tiffany Lynn Jelinski in court with attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Status conference conducted.   Parties stipulate restitution in the amount of $2,000.00 payable to Norlene R.  Defendant to pay at the rate of $100.00 per month commencing May 1, 2016 and to continue on the first day of each month thereafter until paid in full; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment. Defendant Tiffany Lynn Jelinski in court with student intern John Gigot, under the supervision of attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz.  Defendant Tiffany Lynn Jelinski in custody.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  

The Court sentenced defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Corrections, with Huber release privileges for work, with credit for 18 days time served.  

-Court WAIVED all Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments as defendant was ordered to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments on case 14CF5255
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample, however, Court WAIVES the related surcharge as defendant was ordered to pay related surcharges on case 14CF5255
-Defendant is to have no contact with Norleen R.
